2. One Company Each: Startup, SME & Multinational

Startup - Revolut
Founded in 2015 in London, Revolut is a digital banking platform offering currency exchange, international payments, cryptocurrency, and savings features. With approximately 8,000 employees and a valuation of $45 billion (2024), Revolut is one of Europe's most prominent fintech scale-ups. Its rapid international expansion and continued product development firmly place it in the startup/scale-up category.

SME - Macknade
Macknade is an independent fine food retailer based in Kent, United Kingdom. With approximately 100-200 employees, it operates as a family-run business with a regional presence across the South East. Macknade exemplifies the typical SME structure: owner-managed, community-focused, and with a strong local brand identity built over decades.

Multinational - Apple Inc.
Founded in 1976 and headquartered in Cupertino, California, Apple operates across 175+ countries. Its product range includes iPhone, Mac, iPad, Apple Watch, and services like the App Store and Apple Music. With a revenue of approximately $383 billion (2023) and over 160,000 employees, Apple is one of the most valuable multinational corporations in the world.


3. Market Analysis: Work Placement Opportunities
The table below compares work placement opportunities across each company type, outlining key benefits and methods for finding placements.

Company Type	Placement Benefits	How to Find
Startup	Flexible, broad exposure, direct mentorship	LinkedIn, AngelList, Wellfound, company websites
SME	Hands-on, varied roles, close-knit teams	Indeed, local job boards, direct outreach
Multinational	Structured programmes, global exposure, networking	Graduate schemes (e.g. IBM, Google, Deloitte)

Key Insight: Multinationals offer the most structured formal placement schemes (e.g. IBM P-Tech, Deloitte Bright Start, Google internship programme). Startups and scale-ups provide more informal but highly valuable placements where interns often take on real responsibilities early. SMEs are frequently overlooked yet offer excellent experience with broader responsibilities and closer mentorship.


4. One Company Identified for Each Type

Startup - Canva
Canva is an Australian online graphic design platform founded in 2013. With approximately 4,000 employees and a valuation of $26 billion, Canva has grown rapidly by making professional design accessible to non-designers. It competes directly with established players like Adobe and is widely regarded as one of the world's most successful product-led startups.

SME - Bam Bamboo Clothing
Bam Bamboo Clothing is a sustainable clothing brand based in Gloucestershire, UK. With approximately 50-150 employees, Bam sells ethically produced bamboo clothing online and in stores across the United Kingdom. Its focus on sustainability, fair trade, and environmental responsibility has earned it a loyal customer base and strong brand recognition within the UK market.

Multinational - Microsoft
Founded in 1975 and headquartered in Redmond, Washington, Microsoft operates in over 190 countries. Its portfolio includes Windows, Azure cloud services, Office 365, Xbox, LinkedIn, and GitHub. With a revenue of approximately $211 billion (2023) and over 220,000 employees worldwide, Microsoft is one of the most diversified and impactful technology multinationals globally.


